FBIS3-33950 "drnes022_k_94007" FBIS-NES-94-022 Document Type:Daily Report 2 Feb 1994 IRAQ Saddam Views as Baghdad Mayor, Governors Sworn In JN3001163994 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in Arabic 1500 GMT 30 Jan 94 JN3001163994 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network Language: Arabic Article Type:BFN [Text] Tahir Muhammad Hassun has been sworn in before leader President Saddam Husayn upon assuming his duties as mayor of Baghdad. Ghazi Ahmad Khattab, Staff Lieutenant General 'Abd-al-Wahid Shannan Al Ribat, and Mani' 'Abd-Rashid were also sworn in before leader President Saddam Husayn upon assuming their duties as governors of Salah al-Din, Ninawa, and al-Anbar Governorates respectively. The swearing-in ceremony was attended by Hatim Hamdan al-'Azzawi, head of the Presidential Office, and Watban Ibrahim al-Hasan, the minister of interior.
